.TH "pci_legacy_write" 9 "pci_legacy_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_legacy_write \- perform a legacy I/O write
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_legacy_write
.BI "(struct pci_bus *bus "  ","
.BI "u16 port "  ","
.BI "u32 val "  ","
.BI "u8 size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
bus pointer
.IP "port" 12
port to write
.IP "val" 12
value to write
.IP "size" 12
number of bytes to write from \fIval\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Simply writes \fIsize\fP bytes of \fIval\fP to \fIport\fP.
